{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"db50eb8d-5dc1-4d3d-b710-dd411ae916b3","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9**, so you can use the modern patterns:\n\n**`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (preferred in v3+):\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous init here\n    }\n\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test init here\n        await SomeService.InitializeAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — sync init + `TestContext` injection (MSTest v3+ feature).\n- **`[TestInitialize] async Task`** — async per-test init (runs before each test).\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — one-time async class-level init (static, takes `TestContext` param).\n- The property `TestContext { get; }` also makes it available to the test framework for logging via `TestContext.WriteLine`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"782b0e49-4862-4bbf-8b0d-2028e5f8adcb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9. In modern MSTest (v3+), the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use a constructor parameter or a `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property. In MSTest v3+, constructor injection is preferred.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method or constructor.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v2+).\n\nLet me give a concise, accurate answer.\n\nIn MSTest 3.x, the recommended patterns are:\n\n\n- `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (preferred in v3+) or via property.\n- `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` for class-level setup/teardown.\n- `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` for per-test setup/teardown, which support `async Task`.\n\nFor constructor injection of TestContext in MSTest v3, you simply add a `TestContext` parameter to the constructor.","outputTokens":564},"id":"7f5c8060-a3cd-4628-be6f-c7785a415030","timestamp":"2026-04-05T02:00:33.584Z","parentId":"d152c60d-5749-4816-b395-b6e0b5ae5e91"}
